		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Color grading</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Color grading</b> is the process of altering and enhancing the color of a <a href="/wiki/Film" title="Film">motion picture</a> or television image, either electronically, photo-chemically or digitally. The <a href="/wiki/Photochemistry" title="Photochemistry">photo-chemical</a> process is also referred to as <b>color timing</b> and is typically performed at a <a href="/wiki/Photography" title="Photography">photographic</a> <a href="/wiki/Laboratory" title="Laboratory">laboratory</a>. Modern color correction, whether for theatrical film or video distribution, is generally done digitally.</p>
